.NET Core (US-listed pharmaceutical company, Contractor position, Fluent in spoken English)
Responsibilities:
1. Participate in the backend R&D of software products, including data design, data modeling, functional design, and interface code writing;
2. Able to independently complete the development work of modules;
3. Complete the functional design, code implementation, coding, and unit testing of functional modules according to the plan;
4. Strictly abide by the company's coding standards and development requirements for product development;
5 ...

Responsibilities
 Based on user needs, be responsible for the planning and design of the core products for a Perp (Perpetual Contract) exchange;
 Sort out and optimize business processes such as trading, clearing, and interactive display, and drive the implementation of product design and development;
 Be responsible for the full lifecycle management of product features, ensuring the integrity and consistency of feature launches;
 Participate in and follow up on the 0 → 1 construction process of the Perp exchange;
 Explore new industry directions, and regularly produce research reports and competitive analysis;

Requirements
 Experience with exchange or Web3 products;
 Familiar with the core logic of digital asset derivatives, perpetual contracts, order matching, etc.;
 Possess strong logical analysis skills and systematic thinking;
 Possess good project management and cross-departmental collaboration skills;
 Proficient in English for work communication.

Bonus Points
 Product design / operations experience at a well-known CEX or DEX;
 Experience in advancing early-stage products from 0 to 1;
 Understanding of blockchain interaction logic or experience with smart contracts.
